        <h3>About the Event</h3>
        <p>Welcome to ArchX ‚Äì The Ultimate Bridge Challenge presented by NIRMANIKA, the Civil Department of GCOEJ. This event is designed for passionate engineers and enthusiasts to create stable bridges that can sustain loads. Our mission is to push the boundaries of civil engineering through creative ingenuity and teamwork. Join us as we explore new horizons in technical events.</p>

        <h3>Event Rules</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>Each group (2 participants) will be provided with 120 ice cream sticks, glue, and a cutter.</li>
            <li>The bridge must be self-supporting and stand independently on the testing platform.</li>
            <li>The span length must be 45 cm, and the gap must be 40 cm.</li>
            <li>The bridge must have a width of 12 cm to allow weight placement.</li>
            <li>The height must be between 10 cm and 15 cm, and weight limits will be specified by the organizers.</li>
            <li>The bridge must allow for load testing placement at the center.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Judging Criteria</h3>
        <ul>
            <li>The bridge must hold a gradually increasing load until failure. Bridges with correct dimensions are valid.</li>
            <li>The maximum load sustained before breaking determines the score.</li>
            <li>Load will be applied incrementally until failure.</li>
            <li>Testing will be done using hanging weights, sandbags, or a universal testing machine.</li>
        </ul>

